WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.250
A Word Cloud slide lets participants submit words and phrases, and displays them all on screen — with the most popular growing largest at the centre.

2
00:00:08.250 --> 00:00:10.600
Click New Presentation to open a fresh deck.

3
00:00:10.600 --> 00:00:14.540
Select Word Cloud from the slide type picker — it's in the Interactive section.

4
00:00:14.540 --> 00:00:18.800
Type the prompt your audience will respond to. A short, open-ended question works best.

5
00:00:18.800 --> 00:00:27.710
Choose how many words each participant can submit — from 1 to 10. The default of 3 is a great starting point. You'll also find options for a time limit, profanity filter, and hiding results in the same panel.

6
00:00:27.710 --> 00:00:30.640
Click Preview to see how the cloud looks before you go live.

7
00:00:30.640 --> 00:00:36.520
On the participant screen, audience members type their words and tap Submit — watch the cloud react instantly.

8
00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:41.850
As responses come in, the cloud builds live — the more often a word is submitted, the bigger it grows.

9
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.330
Each word lands in the cloud in a random colour, and the most-submitted word grows biggest at the centre.

10
00:00:47.330 --> 00:00:50.750
Exit preview and head back to the editor to fine-tune your settings.

11
00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:59.710
That's your Word Cloud slide set up. Hit Present — participants join on their phones, type their responses, and tap Submit. The cloud builds in real time right in front of the whole room.
